title: Luxor, Egypt
medium: Charcoal pencil and white chalk on blue-gray wove paper
description: Interior of a columned hall, with a series of arches springing transversely from the columns. Braces at the level of the capitals run at right angles to one another. Signed and dated, lower right: "March 8th/90/Luxor/E. Vedder.."
